    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "fOXZU",
      "x": 8600,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 06 Character System",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "rjM8A",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s6title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "5. The Character System",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "OO0Nl",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s6text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Every topic becomes a character. Every character becomes a content universe.\n\nThe system turns cultural topics into repeatable media objects.\n\nTopic\nWine, lavash, duduk, mountains, Yerevan, monasteries, hidden villages.\n\nCharacter\nA voice, mood, emoji, visual style, and emotional role.\n\nStory\nFacts, myths, places, people, rituals, and memory.\n\nFormats\nReels, carousels, stories, guides, maps, newsletters, short films.\n\nTrip Layer\nRoutes, recommendations, booking intent, curated experiences.\n\nExample:\nDuduk\nNot an instrument.\nA voice.\nA sound that feels older than the room.",
