    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "d9Hkd",
      "x": 10320,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 07 Brand Language",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "O0quU",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s7title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "6. The Brand Language",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "DkgaP",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s7text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Say hello to Armenia, one character at a time.\n\nThe identity is modular.\n\nOne brand name.\n\nMany faces.\n\nExamples:\nhelloiam🍷am\nSay hello to Armenian wine.\n\nhelloiam⛰️am\nSay hello to mountains that breathe.\n\nhelloiam🎶am\nSay hello to the sound of duduk.\n\nhelloiam🥖am\nSay hello to lavash, the bread that remembers.\n\nThe emoji becomes a switch.\n\nThe country becomes a cast.\n\nThe brand stays simple, but the system keeps expanding.",
          "lineHeight": 1.18,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 20
        },
