    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "UgnX6",
      "x": 12040,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 08 Content Engine",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "nCW7G",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s8title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "7. The Content Engine",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "nx9XK",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s8text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "From cultural fragments to repeatable media formats.\n\nMeet Armenia is not a random travel blog.\n\nIt is a content factory built around repeatable rubrics.\n\nHello, I Am Armenian [Topic]\nA mass-entry format for introducing cultural themes through short videos, carousels, and story packs.\n\nHidden Armenia\nRare places, micro-stories, and discoveries that make the country feel personal and alive.\n\nSay Hello To...\nMood-led teasers around wine, mountains, food, music, traditions, cities, and routes.\n\nMeet the Character\nA character card for each theme: personality, mood, habits, visual world, and where to meet it.\n\nYour Armenia Type\nA format that turns audience behaviour into travel preferences.",
          "lineHeight": 1.2,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 21
        },
        {
