    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "eVwNL",
      "x": 13760,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 09 Visual Identity",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "bZrSP",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s9title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "8. The Visual Identity System",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "yMfJm",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s9text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "A modular identity for a modular country brand.\n\nThe visual system is built to scale across characters, topics, and formats.\n\nCore elements:\n- dynamic helloiam[emoji]am logo\n- emoji as a theme switcher\n- short slogans built around Say hello to...\n- warm, minimal, cultural visual style\n- cover grids for carousels and stories\n- repeatable layouts for reels, guides, and maps\n- custom character icons over time\n\nThe identity is not fixed.\n\nIt behaves like Armenia itself:\n\none name, many faces.",
          "lineHeight": 1.25,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 24
        },
        {
