    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "oXmDJ",
      "x": 17200,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 11 Business Model",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "VBWya",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s11title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "10. The Business Model",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "IHufu",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s11text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Content → Emotion → Intent → Trip\n\nMeet Armenia is designed as a media-first travel company.\n\n1. Content\nShort videos, carousels, guides, stories, maps, newsletters, and cultural formats.\n\n2. Emotion\nThe audience begins to feel the country, not just learn facts about it.\n\n3. Intent\nPeople start saying: I want to go there, I want to try this, I want this route.\n\n4. Trip\nThe brand converts attention into routes, partners, bookings, tours, and local products.\n\nMain principle:\nMedia brand first.\nTravel company second.\n\nRevenue channels:\n- affiliate and commission from travel bookings\n- curated trips and city breaks\n- wine, food, culture, and nature routes\n- paid guides and premium itineraries\n- brand partnerships\n- sponsored cultural content\n- merchandise and printed guides\n- B2B white-label products for tourism boards, airlines, hotels, and cultural partners",
          "lineHeight": 1.2,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 21
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "U7whIt",
      "x": 18920,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 12 Go To Market",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "fAqeM",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s12title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "11. Go-To-Market",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "SoHGT",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s12text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Start with attention. Convert later.\n\nPhase 1: Media Proof\nLaunch core rubrics: Wine, Duduk, Lavash, Mountains, Hidden Armenia, Yerevan.\n\nPhase 2: Audience & Data\nMeasure what people save, share, comment on, and click.\n\nPhase 3: Trip Intent\nLaunch mini-guides, email, Telegram, and web-based route recommendations.\n\nPhase 4: Travel Products\nBuild partner routes, curated tours, city breaks, and cultural packages.\n\nPhase 5: Platform / IP\nTurn the model into a repeatable system for other countries and regions.\n\nThe sequence is simple:\nAttention first.\nData second.\nTravel products third.",
          "lineHeight": 1.25,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 24
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "JjZtz",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 700,
          "name": "s12road",
          "width": 1408,
          "height": 130,
          "fill": "#00000000",
          "gap": 12,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "p13u6b",
