    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "X3Hkk",
      "x": 20640,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 13 Why Armenia First",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "xZxTc",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s13title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "12. Why Armenia First",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "k4hRV",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s13text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Armenia has unusually high cultural density per square kilometre.\n\nArmenia is small enough to explore.\n\nDeep enough to never finish.\n\nIt has:\n- ancient culture\n- Christian heritage and monasteries\n- mountains and dramatic roads\n- Yerevan as a city-break destination\n- food, wine, and music\n- strong diaspora energy\n- underused global recognition\n- growing accessibility\n- a European cultural and political frame\n\nArmenia is not empty space waiting for a campaign.\n\nIt is already full of characters.\n\nThe work is to introduce them properly.",
          "lineHeight": 1.23,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 23
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "jcrc0",
      "x": 22360,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 14 Competitive Difference",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "H7Tp4t",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s14title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "13. Competitive Difference",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "cA6EE",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s14text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "Not a tourism board. Not a travel agency. Not another Instagram guide.\n\nTourism boards show the country from above.\n\nTravel agencies sell trips from below.\n\nInstagram guides collect nice places.\n\nMeet Armenia builds emotional attachment.\n\nIt does not list attractions.\n\nIt creates characters people can care about.\n\nThe difference:\n\nWe do not show Armenia as a destination.\n\nWe introduce Armenia as someone you can meet.",
          "lineHeight": 1.25,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 25
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "q9AwjM",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 650,
          "name": "s14cols",
          "width": 1408,
          "height": 190,
          "fill": "#00000000",
          "gap": 16
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "XoJZY",
      "x": 24080,
      "y": 13000,
      "name": "Meet Armenia 15 Market Timing",
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1600,
      "height": 900,
      "fill": "$brand-dark",
      "layout": "none",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "J6f7O",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 70,
          "name": "s15title",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "content": "14. Market Timing",
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 52,
          "fontWeight": "700"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "tw9Ui",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 160,
          "name": "s15text",
          "fill": "$brand-white",
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
          "width": 1408,
          "content": "The window is opening.\n\nSeveral forces are moving in the same direction:\n- Armenia is already visible in international travel media.\n- Tourism has recovered and continues to grow.\n- Travellers are looking beyond overexposed destinations.\n- Direct London–Yerevan access is launching.\n- Armenia is progressing through the EU visa liberalisation process.\n- Cultural identity is becoming a stronger driver of travel decisions.\n\nThis creates a rare opening:\n\nA country with depth.\n\nA market looking for new stories.\n\nA media model built for emotional discovery.",
          "lineHeight": 1.25,
          "fontFamily": "$sans",
          "fontSize": 24
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "oLOIy",
          "x": 96,
          "y": 700,
          "name": "s15line",
          "width": 1408,
          "height": 130,
          "fill": "$brand-dark-soft",
          "cornerRadius": 12,
          "layout": "none",
          "children": [
